{{Infobox glacier | child = | name = Agalina Glacier | other_name = | photo = Ant-pen-map-Pefaur-Ventimiglia.PNG | photo_width = | photo_alt = | photo_caption = Location of Pefaur (Ventimiglia) Peninsula on Danco Coast, Antarctic Peninsula | map = Antarctica | map_width = | map_alt = | map_caption = Location of Agalina Glacier in [[Antarctica]] | mark = Blue_pog.svg | type = low gradient | location = [[Danco Coast]] | coordinates = {{coord|64|26|20|S|61|26|00|W|region:AQ|format=dms|display=inline}} | coords_ref = | area = | length = {{convert|4.8|km|mi|abbr=on}} | width = {{convert|2.9|km|mi|abbr=on}} | thickness = | elevation_max = | elevation_min = | terminus = [[Graham Passage]] | status = | embedded = }}
'''Agalina Glacier''' ({{lang-bg|ледник Агалина|translit=Lednik Agalina}} \'led-nik a-ga-'li-na\) is a {{convert|4.8|km|abbr=on}} long and {{convert|2.9|km|abbr=on}} wide glacier on [[Pefaur (Ventimiglia) Peninsula]], [[Danco Coast]] on the west side of [[Antarctic Peninsula]], situated east of [[Poduene Glacier]] and west of [[Krapets Glacier]]. It drains northwards, and flows into both [[Graham Passage]] and the west arm of [[Salvesen Cove]].
The glacier is named after [[Agalina Point]] on the [[Bulgarian Black Sea Coast]].
==Location== Agalina Glacier is centred at {{coord|64|26|20|S|61|26|00|W|display=inline,title}}. [[UK|British]] mapping in 1978.
